<% include ./partials/header %>

<div class="main-banner"></div>

<div class="ui text container">
  <h1>Show Me Things</h1>
  <h3> (this is the index page) </h3>
  <p> Yep, it's true</p>
  <p> Maybe you can try to embed a youtube video of something tech-related</p>
  <p> Blog post: <%= data[0].title %> </p>

  <iframe 
    width="560" 
    height="315" 
    src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/<%= data[0].video %>?autoplay=0&cc_load_policy=1&color=white&controls=1&showinfo=1&rel=0"    
    frameborder="0" 
    allowfullscreen
  >
  </iframe>

  <% data.forEach((article) => { %>
    <div class="item container">
      <h3><%= article.title %></h3>
      <img src="<%= article.image %>" style="height:15em">
      <span><%= article.timestamp %></span>
      <iframe 
        width="560" 
        height="315" 
        src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/<%= article.video %>"    
        frameborder="1" 
        allowfullscreen
      >
      </iframe>
      <p><%= article.info %></p>
      <a class="ui floated basic violet button" href="/things/<%= article._id %>">
        Read More <i class="right chevron icon big"></i>
      </a>
    </div>
    <br>


  <% }); %>

  <br>
  <p> :D </p>
  <p> For the real thing, only stick in the iframe embeds for the latest 3 (or 6 or w/e), and just have a blog link to the other ones (or else it'll slow down too much) </p>
  <p> Don't worry much about the create route, because you'll try to automate that process later </p>
  <p>~</p>
  <p></p>
</div>

<% include ./partials/footer %>
